[15:37:44     1] For FFI entry points, the following rules apply:
[15:37:44     1] - You must not change the signature. FFI entry point signatures must remain exactly as-is to ensure ABI compatibility with the current version of the code. Don't remove `unsafe` or `extern "C"` qualifiers from FFI entry points.
[15:37:44     1] - For struct types that appear only behind a pointer, you may assume the struct is opaque to the user of the library (unless otherwise indicated within the code itself), as is considered best practice in C. This means the struct layout is not part of the ABI, so you may freely change the field types to improve safety.
