[15:42:16    77] +- Converted simple creators (`cJSON_CreateNull`, `True`, `False`, `Bool`, `Number`, `StringReference`, `ObjectReference`, `ArrayReference`, `Array`, `Object`) to build item values before allocation.
[15:42:16    77] +- Changed internal `cJSON_New_Item` from `unsafe extern "C"` to a normal Rust helper; the custom-hook allocation/raw write boundary remains inside it.
[15:42:16    77]  
[15:42:16    77]  Notes / pitfalls:
[15:42:16    77] -- `unsafe_json/cjson.json` is a fixed baseline for the turn and is not rewritten by `cargo check-unsafe2`; it can mention old details or removed wrappers.
[15:42:16    77] -- Do not reintroduce the removed parse/print forwarders; their exported shims now perform the same one-line dispatch directly.
[15:42:16    77] -- `cJSON_New_Item` still contains the hook allocation/raw write boundary. Do not remove custom hooks or switch this to plain `Box` unless hook behavior is preserved for FFI-created items.
[15:42:16    77] +- `unsafe_json/cjson.json` can retain stale entries for removed wrappers during this turn; rely on source and `cargo check-unsafe2` pass/fail for new-code validation.
[15:42:16    77] +- Do not reintroduce removed forwarding wrappers; their exported shims now perform the same dispatch directly.
[15:42:16    77] +- `cJSON_New_Item` still contains the hook allocation/raw write boundary. Do not switch FFI-created items to plain `Box` unless custom hook behavior is preserved.
[15:42:16    77]  - Do not change string/raw creator allocation order casually: allocating the item before duplicating the string preserves cleanup behavior with custom hooks.
[15:42:16    77]  - Do not retry object lookup by moving `CStr::from_ptr` directly into `get_object_item`; a prior run found it increased unsafe counts.
[15:42:16    77]  - Do not retry array accessor cleanup until `cJSON.next`/`child` ownership is redesigned.
[15:42:16    77]  - Avoid new `NonNull` fields or closure patterns returning raw pointers; the checker has flagged those as new unsafe-adjacent surface.
[15:42:16    77]  
[15:42:16    77]  Remaining:
[15:42:16    77] -- `cJSON_New_Item` still owns the hook allocation/raw write boundary.
[15:42:16    77] -- `cJSON_free` still has an implementation unsafe call and two internal callers (`cJSON_SetValuestring`, `replace_item_in_object`); do not move its hook call into those callers unless it is part of a broader safe string/ownership refactor, or the unsafe count may simply move rather than decrease.
[15:42:16    77] -- `cJSON_CreateString` and `cJSON_CreateRaw` still allocate an item first and then duplicate into raw fields; migrate only with a plan that preserves custom-hook allocation/free behavior.
[15:42:16    77] +- Other forwarding wrappers likely remain and can be removed in small batches when no Rust implementation caller needs them.
[15:42:16    77] +- `cJSON_GetArraySize` still performs raw list traversal in an implementation function; a real safe conversion needs list ownership redesigned.
[15:42:16    77] +- `cJSON_New_Item`, `cJSON_free`, `cJSON_CreateString`, and `cJSON_CreateRaw` still depend on custom hook allocation/free behavior.
[15:42:16    77]  - Larger remaining work is in parser/printer/list ownership (`cJSON.next`/`prev`/`child`, `valuestring`/`string`, `printbuffer.buffer`) and allocation hooks.
